<title type="html"><![CDATA[Mirroring...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=202&amp;p=1280#p1280"><![CDATA[
It means where 2 addresses point to the same memory location.<br /><br />The main example is with the nametables.  There's addresses for 4 nametables, but normally only memory for 2 of them.  "horizontal mirroring" would mean that writing to (VRAM) $2000 would be the same as writing to $2400.  Or with vertical mirroring, writing to $2000 and $2800 would be the same.<br /><br />It also applies to the NES's RAM ($0000-$07FF).  Writing to $0900 would be the same as $0100.<br /><br />I hope my explanation makes sense.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Sat Feb 19, 2005 12:39 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
